Generating new ssh keys:

	$ ssh-agent -t rsa -b 4096 "your_mail@example.com"
		
		[When prompt "Enter a file..." press Enter]
		[When prompt "Enter passphrase...", enter Password]

Starting ssh-agent:

	$ eval $(ssh-agent -s)

		[must prompt "Agent pid 5957"]

Adding SSH-key to ssh-agent:

	$ ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa

Showing ssh pub-key:

	cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

Copypasting the output to the GitHub personal settings (New SSH key)

